race.comment: LAUREL HILL (4) has been in the placings ten times in the past 12 months but a win has eluded her. Tackled the Cootamundra Cup over a mile last start and did a reasonable job to finish fourth. Coming back in trip is a positive move. Finds a nice race and this might be her day. MISS FLEETWOOD (10) was lining up for just the fourth time when she bolted in at Nowra in a 1200m maiden last time out. In good hands and looks ready to take this rather large next step. LISTINS LASS (5) produced an eye-catcher at her latest appearance, coming from worse than midfield on the bend to be beaten under a length over 1200m at Kembla. Ready to peak at the third run back over an extra 100m. Lightly raced mare PARIAH ENGAGEMENT (9) resumes. Hasn't won since her debut 13 months ago. Draws the fence and can feature while fresh. WANDAYE (6) didn't quite run a strong 1400m at Goulburn last time so this looks an ideal trip.
